<subSubSection pageId="112" pageNumber="113" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="112.[151,1436,158,774]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[291,547,275,301]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" pagination="5 - 37" refId="ref146755" refString="Rondani, C. (1869 a) Ortalidinae italicae collectae, distinctae et in ordinem dispositae. Dipterologiae italicae prodromi. Pars VII - Fasc. 3. Linea A. Ortaloidi. Dipter. Stirps XX. Ortalidinae Rndn. Bullettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 1, 5 - 37. [January] [Dated from Poggi (2008).]" type="journal article" year="1869">Rondani (1869a: 32)</bibRefCitation>
did not explicitly replace 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen, 1803" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1803" box="[890,1206,275,301]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Platystoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[890,1022,276,301]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Platystoma</emphasis>
Meigen, 1803
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1869" box="[1287,1428,276,301]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Megaglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1287,1428,276,301]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Megaglossa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Instead, he proposed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1869" box="[504,646,315,340]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Megaglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[504,646,315,340]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Megaglossa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the name for the generic concept of “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Mgn. (1803) Macq. Wlk." authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1803" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Platystoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
Platystoma 
<emphasis box="[1286,1340,315,340]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Mgn</emphasis>
. (1803) 
<emphasis box="[247,314,354,379]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Macq</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[331,376,354,379]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Wlk</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicName>
etc. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1838" box="[445,555,354,380]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Trupanea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Trupanea</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[566,581,354,379]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">p</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[598,652,354,379]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Schr</emphasis>
. — Dyctia 
<emphasis box="[797,811,354,379]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">p</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[829,888,354,379]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Fabr</emphasis>
. — 
<taxonomicName box="[945,1023,354,380]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Musca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Musca</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1033,1047,354,379]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">p</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1065,1128,354,379]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Rossi</emphasis>
. Hesyquillia? 
<emphasis box="[1304,1362,354,379]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Desv</emphasis>
.” and provided a footnote explaining that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1803" box="[681,813,393,418]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Platystoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[681,813,393,418]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Platystoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was also used by Klein, 1753 [which, being a pre- Linnaean name not used after 1758 as an available name, does not enter into nomenclature and cannot be a senior homonym]. The wording quoted above has been interpreted by subsequent catalogers as Rondani explicitly proposing 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1869" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1869" box="[598,920,510,536]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Megaglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[598,740,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Megaglossa</emphasis>
Rondani, 1869
</taxonomicName>
as a new replacement name for 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen, 1803" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1803" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Platystoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1304,1436,510,535]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Platystoma</emphasis>
Meigen, 1803
</taxonomicName>
and we have chosen to follow this. The alternative interpretation, that 
<taxonomicName authority="Rondani, 1869" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Megaglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1294,1435,549,574]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Megaglossa</emphasis>
Rondani, 1869
</taxonomicName>
was proposed as a separate genus and not as a new replacement name, would render 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen, 1826" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1826" box="[247,687,631,657]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Platystoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umbrarum">
<emphasis box="[247,511,631,656]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Platystoma umbrarum</emphasis>
Meigen, 1826
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[777,827,631,657]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">type</typeStatus>
species for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1869" box="[975,1116,631,656]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Megaglossa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[975,1116,631,656]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Megaglossa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by original designation of 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[247,478,670,696]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" pagination="5 - 37" refId="ref146755" refString="Rondani, C. (1869 a) Ortalidinae italicae collectae, distinctae et in ordinem dispositae. Dipterologiae italicae prodromi. Pars VII - Fasc. 3. Linea A. Ortaloidi. Dipter. Stirps XX. Ortalidinae Rndn. Bullettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 1, 5 - 37. [January] [Dated from Poggi (2008).]" type="journal article" year="1869">Rondani (1869a: 9)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Meigen, 1826" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1826" box="[490,924,670,696]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Platystoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="umbrarum">
<emphasis box="[490,753,670,695]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Platystoma umbrarum</emphasis>
Meigen, 1826
</taxonomicName>
is treated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Soos, A." box="[1083,1285,670,696]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" pagination="38 - 45" refId="ref150540" refString="Soos, A. (1984 b) Family Platystomatidae, pp. 38 - 45. In: Soos, A. &amp; Papp, L. (eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera. Volume 9. Micropezidae - Agromyzidae. Elsevier Science Publishers, Amsterdam &amp; Akademiai Kiado, Budapest. 460 pp. [15 October] [Dated from Evenhuis (2008 b).]" type="book chapter" year="1984">Soós (1984b: 45)</bibRefCitation>
in “doubtful species” of 
<taxonomicName box="[383,574,709,735]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Platystomatidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
